        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 16 at 2:11PM EDT by NWS Detroit/Pontiac MI</headline>
        <description>At 211 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a cluster of strong
thunderstorms along a line extending from near Forestville to 6 miles
southwest of Argyle to near Kingston. Movement was east at 15 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and half inch hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is
possible.

Strong thunderstorms will be near...
Deckerville around 215 PM EDT.
Sandusky around 230 PM EDT.
Carsonville around 250 PM EDT.

Other locations impacted by these storms include Decker, Palms,
McGregor, Wilmot, Forester, Snover, Juhl, Elmer, and Richmondville.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
